From 1622 Hyeon-jeong Kim from Cheongju
From 3654 Hye-mi Kim from Cheongju

00:28:21.360 --> 00:28:22.490 line:93%
What is all of that?

00:28:22.570 --> 00:28:23.700 line:93%
Jail date.

00:28:24.450 --> 00:28:27.490 line:93%
It's like a pen pal program between jails.

00:28:28.370 --> 00:28:31.000 line:93%
When did that punk start the jail dates?

00:28:31.080 --> 00:28:32.790 line:93%
Yes. Six letters. Six.

00:28:33.920 --> 00:28:35.420 line:93%
Who wants a jail date?

00:28:36.290 --> 00:28:38.380 line:93%
-With whom is it?
-Where else?

00:28:39.050 --> 00:28:40.550 line:93%
Cheongju Female Penitentiary.

00:28:40.840 --> 00:28:44.220 line:93%
It's their cell 2B6 and our cell 2B6.

00:28:46.220 --> 00:28:48.260 line:93%
We got six letters, but no one wants?

00:28:48.350 --> 00:28:49.600 line:93%
First come first served.

00:28:49.680 --> 00:28:51.600 line:93%
You're such trash.

00:28:51.680 --> 00:28:54.100 line:93%
I know already, okay?

00:28:55.730 --> 00:28:57.190 line:93%
Jung-woo, are you in?

00:28:59.770 --> 00:29:01.530 line:93%
Je-hyeok, let's do it.

00:29:01.820 --> 00:29:02.860 line:93%
I have a girlfriend.

00:29:02.940 --> 00:29:05.450 line:93%
You do? Really? Okay.

00:29:06.110 --> 00:29:09.490 line:93%
Min-chul, aren't you lonely? Join.

00:29:09.580 --> 00:29:11.330 line:93%
Knock yourself out.

00:29:12.830 --> 00:29:15.330 line:93%
-How about you, Looney?
-I'm seeing someone too.

00:29:15.420 --> 00:29:19.170 line:93%
God. Forget it. Fine.
I'll take them all. All of them.

00:29:25.090 --> 00:29:26.010 line:93%
You want in?

00:29:28.140 --> 00:29:30.720 line:93%
He's Trash Number Two.

00:29:31.260 --> 00:29:33.600 line:93%
Okay. Come here. Pick.

00:29:33.680 --> 00:29:35.180 line:93%
Pick one.

00:29:35.270 --> 00:29:38.150 line:93%
Hold on. I can pick first, right?

00:29:38.230 --> 00:29:39.980 line:93%
I... I want...

00:29:40.650 --> 00:29:42.360 line:93%
<i>A broadcast shared with 50,000 inmates.</i>

00:29:42.440 --> 00:29:45.070 line:93%
<i>I am Min-joo Lee, your host
of the Borami Broadcast.</i>

00:29:45.650 --> 00:29:47.740 line:93%
<i>The summer is almost over as well.</i>

00:29:47.820 --> 00:29:50.280 line:93%
<i>Many things come to mind
when I hear "August."</i>

00:29:50.660 --> 00:29:53.410 line:93%
<i>Summer vacation, vacations, trips,</i>

00:29:53.490 --> 00:29:55.750 line:93%
<i>hurricanes, monsoons, and the beach.</i>

00:29:56.250 --> 00:30:00.380 line:93%
<i>As for me, I like the word
"vacation" the most.</i>

00:30:01.000 --> 00:30:04.460 line:93%
<i>Are you sad that you can't go on vacation?</i>

00:30:04.760 --> 00:30:06.010 line:93%
<i>Don't be sad.</i>

00:30:06.090 --> 00:30:09.340 line:93%
<i>Going somewhere isn't the only way
you can take a vacation.</i>

00:30:09.720 --> 00:30:11.260 line:93%
<i>Here's the last song for today.</i>

00:30:11.350 --> 00:30:14.020 line:93%
<i>Why don't we all go on a vacation
for a few minutes</i>

00:30:14.310 --> 00:30:17.310 line:93%
<i>along with this song? "The Pearl Fishers."</i>

00:30:21.230 --> 00:30:23.320 line:93%
Can you not read?

00:30:24.320 --> 00:30:27.150 line:93%
How many months are you reading
<i>Romance of the Three Kingdoms</i>?

00:30:28.740 --> 00:30:30.530 line:93%
It's my girlfriend's favorite book.

00:30:31.530 --> 00:30:36.500 line:93%
She read it over ten times,
so I want to try reading it.

00:30:38.330 --> 00:30:40.670 line:93%
You should've been good while you had her.

00:30:50.050 --> 00:30:53.600 line:93%
I regret everything after coming here.

00:30:54.390 --> 00:30:57.060 line:93%
I should've been better to my lover.

00:30:57.930 --> 00:31:02.190 line:93%
Why did I take drugs and end up
being separated from the person I love?

00:31:03.860 --> 00:31:07.360 line:93%
I mean, how am I in jail, of all places?

00:31:08.240 --> 00:31:10.240 line:93%
My life is a mess.

00:31:16.160 --> 00:31:19.910 line:93%
He must really like prison.

00:31:45.610 --> 00:31:46.570 line:93%
Goodness...

00:31:47.570 --> 00:31:49.070 line:93%
He's excited.

00:31:49.900 --> 00:31:50.900 line:93%
When will you grow up?

00:31:55.410 --> 00:31:57.370 line:93%
I'm over 50 years old.
If I were going to grow up,

00:31:57.450 --> 00:31:59.250 line:93%
I would've grown up long ago.

00:31:59.660 --> 00:32:02.580 line:93%
And if you grow up, you die.

00:32:03.880 --> 00:32:06.630 line:93%
-Are you proud of being in jail?
-Of course.

00:32:07.380 --> 00:32:11.050 line:93%
A real man should collect stars
while he's alive.

00:32:11.130 --> 00:32:12.760 line:93%
They're like medals.

00:32:13.510 --> 00:32:17.180 line:93%
You're shameless. So shameless.

00:32:17.720 --> 00:32:19.720 line:93%
How many stars did you say you had?

00:32:20.930 --> 00:32:25.770 line:93%
<i>Ni, er, san, si,
go, roku, shichi, hachi,</i> nine, ten. Peow.

00:32:26.770 --> 00:32:28.270 line:93%
If you have ten priors,

00:32:29.610 --> 00:32:30.900 line:93%
how long were you in prison?

00:32:30.990 --> 00:32:33.910 line:93%
How long? He was here crazy long.

00:32:34.660 --> 00:32:37.660 line:93%
He's an old Jailbird. Old Jailbird.

00:32:37.740 --> 00:32:41.370 line:93%
But Jailbird is more mature than Kaist.

00:32:42.540 --> 00:32:44.620 line:93%
Is it because you were never married?

00:32:44.710 --> 00:32:47.590 line:93%
He was. Six times.

00:32:48.170 --> 00:32:50.420 line:93%
It's because he has no kids.

00:32:50.510 --> 00:32:55.800 line:93%
Even a dirtbag gets his act together
and lives a decent life if he has a kid.

00:32:56.140 --> 00:32:57.260 line:93%
I have a kid.

00:32:59.890 --> 00:33:00.930 line:93%
I have a son.

00:33:01.310 --> 00:33:04.690 line:93%
He should be 21 or 22 by now.

00:33:05.480 --> 00:33:07.310 line:93%
Aren't you ashamed to face your son?

00:33:07.400 --> 00:33:09.360 line:93%
Aren't you ashamed to face your parents?

00:33:09.980 --> 00:33:13.190 line:93%
-Let's not attack family.
-You started it, bastard.

00:33:14.820 --> 00:33:15.660 line:93%
Really?

00:33:16.110 --> 00:33:18.280 line:93%
Then why hasn't your son
come to visit once?

00:33:18.370 --> 00:33:20.950 line:93%
We cut ties long ago.

00:33:21.580 --> 00:33:24.080 line:93%
Anyway, that bastard is a real prick.

